{"title_page": "Cornered (1924 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1924 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Cornered\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[William Beaudine]]\n| producer       = \n| based on       = ''Cornered'' (1920 play) by Dodson Mitchell<br>[[Zelda Sears]]\n| writer         = [[Louis D. Lighton]]<br>[[Hope Loring]]\n| starring       = [[Marie Prevost]]\n| cinematography = [[Ray June]]\n| editing        = \n| studio         = [[Warner Bros.]]\n| distributor    = Warner Bros.\n| released       = {{Film date|1924|8|1}}\n| runtime        = 70 minutes\n|budget=$94,000<ref name=\"warners\">Warner Bros financial information in The William Shaefer Ledger. See Appendix 1, Historical Journal of Film, Radio and Television, (1995) 15:sup1, 1-31 p 3 DOI: 10.1080/01439689508604551</ref>\n|gross=$257,000<ref name=\"warners\"/>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent\n}}\n\n'''''Cornered''''' is a 1924 American [[silent film|silent]] [[drama film]] directed by [[William Beaudine]].<ref>[https://catalog.afi.com/Catalog/moviedetails/3439?sid The AFI Catalog of Feature Films 1893-1993:''Cornered'']</ref><ref name=\"silenthollywood\">{{cite web |url=http://silenthollywood.com/cornered1924.html |title=Cornered (1924) |accessdate=December 14, 2013 |work=Silent Hollywood}}</ref>  It is considered to be a [[lost film|lost]].<ref>[http://lcweb2.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.4430/default.html The Library of Congress American Silent Feature Film Survival Catalog:''Cornered'']</ref> The story was filmed again in 1930 as a talkie called ''[[Road to Paradise (film)|Road to Paradise]]''.  It was also directed by Beaudine. According to Warner Bros records the film earned $235,000 domestically and $22,000 foreign.<ref name=\"warners\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Marie Prevost]] as Mary Brennan / Margaret Waring\n* [[Rockliffe Fellowes]] as Jerry, the Gent\n* [[Raymond Hatton]] as Nick, the Dope\n* [[John Roche (actor)|John Roche]] as George Wells\n* [[Cissy Fitzgerald]] as Lola Mulvaney\n* [[Vera Lewis]] as Mrs. Wells\n* [[George C. Pearce]] as Brewster (as George Pearce)\n* [[Bartine Burkett]] as The Bride\n* [[Billy Bletcher]] as The Groom (as Billy Fletcher)\n* [[Ruth Dwyer (actress)|Ruth Dwyer]] as Mrs. Webster\n* Bertram Johns as Webster\n* [[Wilfred Lucas]] as Updike\n* [[Virginia Marshall]] as Mary Brennan / Margaret Waring as a Child\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0014800|Cornered}}\n* {{tcmdb title|494886|Cornered}}\n\n{{William Beaudine |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cornered}}\n[[Category:1924 films]]\n[[Category:1924 drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:American silent feature films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by William Beaudine]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. films]]\n[[Category:Lost American films]]\n[[Category:1924 lost films]]\n[[Category:Lost drama films]]\n\n\n{{1920s-silent-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1924 film}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Cornered\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[William Beaudine]]\n| producer       = \n| based on       = ''Cornered'' (1920 play) by Dodson Mitchell<br>[[Zelda Sears]]\n| writer         = [[Louis D. Lighton]]<br>[[Hope Loring]]\n| starring       = [[Marie Prevost]]\n| cinematography = [[Ray June]]\n| editing        = \n| studio         = [[Warner Bros.]]\n| distributor    = Warner Bros.\n| released       = {{Film date|1924|8|1}}\n| runtime        = 70 minutes\n|budget=$94,000<ref name=\"warners\">Warner Bros financial information in The William Shaefer Ledger. See Appendix 1, Historical Journal of Film, Radio and Television, (1995) 15:sup1, 1-31 p 3 DOI: 10.1080/01439689508604551</ref>\n|gross=$257,000<ref name=\"warners\"/>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent\n}}\n\n'''''Cornered''''' is a 1924 American [[silent film|silent]] [[drama film]] directed by [[William Beaudine]].<ref>[https://catalog.afi.com/Catalog/moviedetails/3439?sid The AFI Catalog of Feature Films 1893-1993:''Cornered'']</ref><ref name=\"silenthollywood\">{{cite web |url=http://silenthollywood.com/cornered1924.html |title=Cornered (1924) |accessdate=14 December 2013 |work=Silent Hollywood}}</ref>  It is considered to be a [[lost film|lost]].<ref>[http://lcweb2.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.4430/default.html The Library of Congress American Silent Feature Film Survival Catalog:''Cornered'']</ref> The story was filmed again in 1930 as a talkie called ''[[Road to Paradise (film)|Road to Paradise]]''.  It was also directed by Beaudine. According to Warner Bros records the film earned $235,000 domestically and $22,000 foreign.<ref name=\"warners\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Marie Prevost]] as Mary Brennan / Margaret Waring\n* [[Rockliffe Fellowes]] as Jerry, the Gent\n* [[Raymond Hatton]] as Nick, the Dope\n* [[John Roche (actor)|John Roche]] as George Wells\n* [[Cissy Fitzgerald]] as Lola Mulvaney\n* [[Vera Lewis]] as Mrs. Wells\n* [[George C. Pearce]] as Brewster (as George Pearce)\n* [[Bartine Burkett]] as The Bride\n* [[Billy Bletcher]] as The Groom (as Billy Fletcher)\n* [[Ruth Dwyer (actress)|Ruth Dwyer]] as Mrs. Webster\n* Bertram Johns as Webster\n* [[Wilfred Lucas]] as Updike\n* [[Virginia Marshall]] as Mary Brennan / Margaret Waring as a Child\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0014800|Cornered}}\n* {{tcmdb title|494886|Cornered}}\n\n{{William Beaudine |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cornered}}\n[[Category:1924 films]]\n[[Category:1924 drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:American silent feature films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by William Beaudine]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. films]]\n[[Category:Lost 