ey Hotel]]/[[Underground Railway]] Informational Site \n| \n| 46 State Street, northeast corner of State and Griswold streets\n| [[Detroit]]\n| {{dts|1956|8|23}}\n|-\n| [[History of Detroit#1805 fire|Fire of 1805]]\n| \n|\n| [[Detroit]]\n| {{dts|1956|8|23}}\n|-\n| [[First Christian Reformed Church of Detroit]]\n| \n| 1444 Maryland Avenue\n| [[Grosse Pointe Park, Michigan|Grosse Pointe Park]]\n| {{dts|1989|12|20}}\n|-\n| [[First Congregational Church (Detroit, Michigan)|First Congregational Church of Detroit]]\u2020\n| [[File:First Congregational Church (Detroit, Michigan).jpg|100px]]\n| 33 East Forest Street\n| [[Detroit]]\n| {{dts|1974|7|26}}\n|-\n| [[First Congregational Church (Wayne, Michigan)|First Congregational Church]]\n| \n| 2 Towne Square Street\n| [[Wayne, Michigan|Wayne]]\n| {{dts|1999|4|15}}\n|-\n| [[First Detroit Public Library]] Commemorative Designation \n| \n| Griswold and State streets\n| [[Detroit]]\n| {{dts|1964|1|24}}\n|-\n| [[Temple Beth El (Detroit, Michigan)#Early years|First Jewish Religious Services]] Informational Designation\n| \n| Corner of St. Antoine and East Congress\n| [[Detroit]]\n| {{dts|1977|4|1}}\n|-\n| [[102nd Regiment United States Colored Troops|First Michigan Colored Regiment]] Informational Site\n| \n| [[Duffield School]] Ground, 2700 Clinton Street at Joseph Campau\n| [[Detroit]]\n| {{dts|1968|3|1}}\n|-\n| [[First Mile of Concrete Highway]] Informational Designation\n| \n| Woodward Avenue (US-10) between Six and Seven Mile roads, in [[Palmer Park Apartment Building Historic District|Palmer Park]]\n| [[Detroit]]\n| {{dts|1957|1|19}}\n|-\n| [[First Presbyterian Church (Detroit, Michigan)|First Presbyterian Church]]\u2020\n| [[File:First Presbyterian Church Detroit 2.jpg|100px]]\n| 2930 Woodward Avenue\n| [[Detroit]]\n| {{dts|1979|8|3}}\n|-\n| [[First Presbyterian Church of Northville]] Informational Site\n| \n| 200 East Main Street\n| [[Northville, Michigan|Northville]]\n| {{dts|1989|5|18}}\n|-\n| [[Perry McAdow House|First U