{"title_page": "Philadelphia", "text_new": "{{Redirect|Philly||Philly (disambiguation)|and|Philadelphia (disambiguation)}}\n{{pp-semi-indef}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{short description|Largest city in Pennsylvania}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Philadelphia, Pennsylvania\n| official_name                   = City of Philadelphia\n| settlement_type                 = [[Consolidated city-county]]\n| etymology                       = [[Ancient Greek]]: [[wikt:\u03c6\u03af\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2|\u03c6\u03af\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2]] ''ph\u00edlos'' (beloved, dear) and [[wikt:\u1f00\u03b4\u03b5\u03bb\u03c6\u03cc\u03c2|\u1f00\u03b4\u03b5\u03bb\u03c6\u03cc\u03c2]] ''adelph\u00f3s'' (brother, brotherly)\n| image_skyline                   = {{Photomontage\n| photo1a                   = Philadelphia skyline from South Street Bridge January 2020 (rotate 2 degrees perspective correction crop 4-1).jpg\n| photo2a                   = Independence National Historical Park INDE0004 b.jpg{{!}}Liberty Bell and Independence Hall\n| photo2b                   = Philadelphia City Hall - 2.jpg{{!}}City Hall\n| photo3a                   = A359, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, USA, Delancey Street in Society Hill, 2009.JPG{{!}}Delancey Street, Society Hill\n| photo3b                   = North facade of College Hall, Penn Campus.jpg{{!}}College Hall, Penn Campus\n| photo4a                   = PhiladelphiaMuseumOfArt2017.jpg{{!}}Museum of Art\n| spacing                   = 2\n| position                  = center\n| color_border              = black\n| color                     = white\n| size                      = 270\n| foot_montage              = Clockwise from top: [[List of tallest buildings in Philadelphia|Center City skyline]] in 2020; [[Philadelphia City Hall|City Hall]]; [[College Hall (University of Pennsylvania)|College Hall, Penn Campus]]; [[Philadelphia Museum of Art|Museum of Art]]; Delancey Street [[Terraced house|row houses]] in [