elphiaMuseumOfArt2017.jpg{{!}}Museum of Art\n| spacing                   = 2\n| position                  = center\n| color_border              = black\n| color                     = white\n| size                      = 270\n| foot_montage              = Clockwise from top: [[List of tallest buildings in Philadelphia|Center City skyline]] in 2020; [[Philadelphia City Hall|City Hall]]; [[College Hall (University of Pennsylvania)|College Hall, Penn Campus]]; [[Philadelphia Museum of Art|Museum of Art]]; Delancey Street [[Terraced house|row houses]] in [[Society Hill]]; [[Liberty Bell]] and [[Independence Hall]]\n}}\n| nickname                        = \"Philly\", \"The City of Brotherly Love\", \"The [[Athens]] of America\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.librarycompany.org/artifacts/athens.htm|title=Art & Artifacts: Discover the Library Company's Art and Artifact Collection \u2013 Athens of America|website=librarycompany.org|publisher=The Library Company of Philadelphia|accessdate=June 12, 2010}}</ref> <small> and other [[nicknames of Philadelphia]]</small>\n| motto                           = \"Philadelphia maneto\" (\"Let brotherly love endure\" or \"... continue\")<ref>Robinson, Sam (November 5, 2013). [https://hiddencityphila.org/2013/11/behind-philadelphia-maneto-dissecting-the-city-seal/ \"Behind Philadelphia Maneto: Dissecting The City Seal\"]. Hidden City Philadelphia. Retrieved January 18, 2018.</ref><ref>McDevitt, John (May 5, 2015). [http://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2015/05/05/plaque-dedication-marks-120th-anniversary-of-creation-of-philadelphias-flag/ \"Plaque Dedication Marks 120th Anniversary of Creation of Philadelphia\u2019s Flag\"]. philadelphia.cbslocal.com. CBS Broadcasting Inc. Retrieved January 18, 2018.</ref>\n| image_flag                      = Flag of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.svg\n| image_seal                      = Seal of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.svg\n| image_blank_emblem              = City of Philadelphia Logo.svg\n| blank_emblem_size  