 1923\n| isbn = 978-0-486-24511-9\n}}\n* {{cite web | ref = {{harvid|Rules of Evidence|2017}}\n| title = Federal Rules of Evidence\n| website = United States Courts\n| url = http://www.uscourts.gov/sites/default/files/rules-of-evidence.pdf\n| publisher = Federal Judiciary of the United States\n| access-date = November 19, 2017\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171119211308/http://www.uscourts.gov/sites/default/files/rules-of-evidence.pdf\n| archive-date = 2017-11-19\n}}\n* {{cite web | ref = {{harvid|Rule 702 Notes|2011}}\n| title = Federal rules of evidence 702 (Notes)\n| url=https://www.law.cornell.edu/rules/fre/rule_702\n| website = Cornell Law School\n| publisher = Legal Information Institute\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref= harv\n| last = Grayling\n| first = A.C.\n| title = The history of philosophy\n| date = 2019\n| publisher = Penguin\n| isbn = 9780241304556\n}}\n* Feyerabend, Paul K., ''[[Against Method]]: Outline of an Anarchistic Theory of Knowledge'', Humanities Press, London, UK, 1975.  Reprinted, Verso, London, UK, 1978.\n* {{Cite web | ref = harv\n| last = Heath\n| first = Joseph\n| date = 21 January 2015\n| url = http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/methodological-individualism\n| title = Methodological Individualism at the Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy\n| orig-year = First published Feb 3 2005\n}}\n* {{cite journal | ref = harv\n| last1 = Fine\n| first1 = Kit\n| date = 2019\n| title = Verisimilitude and Truthmaking\n| journal = Erkenntnis\n| doi = 10.1007/s10670-019-00152-z\n}}\n* {{cite journal | ref = harv\n| last = Henderson\n| first = Leah\n| date = 2018\n| journal =\n| series =  The Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy\n| title = The Problem of Induction\n| volume =\n| chapter =\n| editor-first = Edward N.\n| editor-last= Zalta\n| publisher = Metaphysics Research Lab, Stanford University\n| edition = Summer 2018\n| pages =\n| url= https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/sum2018/entries/induction-problem\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| las